"choice":416},"ἰείων",{"corr":417,"sic":418},"δ","γ",{"supplied":420},{"_":421,"reason":385,"cert":75},"ἡμῖν",{"_":423,"supplied":424},"ν",{"_":425,"reason":385},"τὴ","ἒνβασιν",{"type":428,"resp":354,"listApp":429},"apparatus",{"app":430},[431,433,435,437,439,443],{"note":432},"Text based on photographs",{"loc":375,"note":434},"Ferrua, Korhonen: ((Chi-rho)); Kaibel: Μ(ᾶρκος)",{"loc":399,"note":436},"Franz: Ῥεστ[ιτ]οῦτος",{"loc":379,"note":438},"Franz: ἠγοράσαμεν; Kaibel, Wessel, Korhonen: ἠγοράσομεν (“mixto imperfecto et aoristo ortum” Kaibel, see also IG 14.96)",{"loc":381,"note":440},{"_":441,"corr":442},"Franz: ἰίων; Kaibel, Wessel, Korhonen: ἰείων",[417,417],{"loc":383,"note":444},{"_":445,"corr":446,"unclear":449},"Franz: ν βάσιν; Kaibel suggested in apparatus ἐν πᾶκι? and Wessel ἐν ac (see also ἐν πάκης in IGCVO 602); Ferrua [ἠμι]ν ἔνβασιν; Korhonen [ἠμι]ν [?] ἔνβασιν (but also τὴ]ν is possible)",[447,448],"τῆ","e","p",{"type":451,"xml:lang":128,"resp":354,"p":452},"translation","((Chi-Rho)) Aurelios Rhestoutos and Zosime, we purchased this tomb at our expense.",{"type":451,"xml:lang":291,"resp":354,"p":454},"((Chi-Rho)) Aurelios Rhestoutos e Zosime, acquistammo questa tomba a nostre spese.",{"type":456,"resp":354,"p":457},"commentary",{"_":458,"ref":459,"foreign":475},"This is a marble plaque and not a sarcophagus, which must have served to mark a “loculus”, according to the interpretation that J. and L. Robert (BE 1964 nr. 631) gave for a similar inscription from Catania, RAC 8 (1931) 122-25 = . This inscription attests to the purchase of the tomb by the deceased who are buried in it: the names of the deceased are followed by the verb , an expression indicating that the purchase was made at their own expense () and by the object (for  as the tomb, see AE 1996.0792 =  and Ferrua 1958: 172). It is possible that there was a reflexive pronoun in the lacuna of l. 6, as in other cases where the deceased purchased the grave for himself: IMusCatania 229 = . For the registration of the purchase of the tomb in Christian epitaphs, see Führer and Schultze (1907: 12-15) and Korhonen (2004: 108-110). The cognomen of the deceased must have been Restitutus but for such a form, see ICUR 19782. The name of the woman, , is attested in other inscriptions of the city (CIL 10.7016 = , IMusCatania 165 = ) and more in general of Sicily (LGPN 3A: 190).",[460,463,466,469,472],{"_":461,"target":462},"ISic001547","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001547",{"_":464,"target":465},"ISic001423","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001423",{"_":467,"target":468},"ISic001628","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001628",{"_":470,"target":471},"ISic000300","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000300",{"_":473,"target":474},"ISic001649","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001649",[476,478,480,482],{"_":477,"xml:lang":112},"ἀγοράω",{"_":479,"xml:lang":112},"ἐκ τῶν ἰδίων",{"_":481,"xml:lang":112},"ἔνβασις",{"_":405,"xml:lang":112},{"type":484,"listBibl":485},"bibliography",[486,559],{"type":370,"bibl":487},[488,496,504,511,519,530,537,544,552],{"author":489,"date":490,"citedRange":491,"ptr":492,"ref":494},"Amico","1741","259 no.15",{"target":493},"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F5INCW3T",{"_":495,"target":495},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002186",{"author":497,"date":498,"citedRange":499,"ptr":500,"ref":502},"Torremuzza","1769","166 no.19",{"target":501},"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/SPTB56H3",{"_":503,"target":503},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084",{"author":497,"date":505,"citedRange":506,"ptr":507,"ref":509},"1784","173 no.19",{"target":508},"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/7PSFHSUH",{"_":510,"target":510},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083",{"author":512,"date":513,"citedRange":514,"ptr":515,"ref":517},"Ferrara","1829","349 no.1",{"target":516},"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/82T4IWDN",{"_":518,"target":518},"https://biblio.i